{
  "text": "In order to understand the duration profile of disability claims, Kaplan-Meier (see [CITATION_1] survival curves have been created for the duration of disability claims. Kaplan-Meier curves can be used to provide a non-parametric estimate of the survival function for claims. The event of interest in this survival analysis is clearly claim termination. The duration variable is used to measure time since claim onset, and not time since payment of disability benefits begins.",
